902
00:52:33,880 --> 00:52:34,640
Really?

903
00:52:35,280 --> 00:52:38,080
Maybe cyanide,

904
00:52:38,240 --> 00:52:40,160
but if there's atropine action,

905
00:52:40,320 --> 00:52:41,880
it's probably digitalis.

906
00:52:42,320 --> 00:52:43,000
And so?

907
00:52:43,160 --> 00:52:45,320
The signs are contradictory.

908
00:52:46,320 --> 00:52:47,360
Yes, and so?

909
00:52:47,560 --> 00:52:50,600
I need to ask another colleague.

910
00:52:50,800 --> 00:52:53,040
Wait, I know someone.

911
00:52:53,200 --> 00:52:56,160
Ah, yes. It's the Snowden of poisons.

912
00:52:56,360 --> 00:52:58,240
The Ricky Gervais
of intestinal lamella.

913
00:52:58,480 --> 00:53:00,600
-Great.
-I'll call him.

914
00:53:06,320 --> 00:53:07,480
Pool...

915
00:53:07,920 --> 00:53:11,360
Pool, pool,
who is the most beautiful cop?

916
00:53:12,920 --> 00:53:13,760
Not me.

917
00:53:33,040 --> 00:53:35,760
CRIMINAL RECORD MANON BECHET.

918
00:53:44,320 --> 00:53:45,800
Are you Manon Bechet ?

919
00:53:46,720 --> 00:53:48,960
National Police,
Captain Marleau.

920
00:53:49,360 --> 00:53:52,600
Bechet... aren't you from Australia?
From Sydney? No?

921
00:53:53,000 --> 00:53:55,480
I've got a frog catcher.

922
00:53:56,080 --> 00:53:57,320
Just wait five minutes.

923
00:53:58,480 --> 00:53:59,520
It's ringing.

924
00:54:02,360 --> 00:54:03,160
No.

925
00:54:03,880 --> 00:54:05,960
I read your file.

926
00:54:06,320 --> 00:54:08,520
You stole bottles of alcohol.

927
00:54:08,720 --> 00:54:11,480
We've all done that. It's no biggie.

928
00:54:11,600 --> 00:54:13,320
But I did notice one thing.

929
00:54:13,520 --> 00:54:16,680
You sold drugs to someone
from the police drug brigade.

930
00:54:18,840 --> 00:54:21,480
And the court gave you
mitigating circumstances

931
00:54:21,640 --> 00:54:22,800
for your stupidity?

932
00:54:24,000 --> 00:54:25,480
Did you come to mock me?

933
00:54:25,840 --> 00:54:27,800
We're not well paid.
We need to laugh.

934
00:54:28,200 --> 00:54:29,760
Otherwise, I also saw

935
00:54:29,920 --> 00:54:31,600
Ms. Dewaere is your reference.

936
00:54:32,840 --> 00:54:35,600
Does she know
about your pink bunny phone?

937
00:54:38,080 --> 00:54:39,040
Speaking of pink,

938
00:54:41,360 --> 00:54:44,160
did someone come
to buy some roses this morning?

939
00:54:44,280 --> 00:54:45,240
Who?

940
00:54:45,480 --> 00:54:46,760
Red roses?

941
00:54:46,920 --> 00:54:48,080
23, I counted them.

942
00:54:50,360 --> 00:54:51,960
Émilie Guingamp, the hairdresser.

943
00:54:52,560 --> 00:54:55,240
-Chalard's mistress?
-Mistress?

944
00:54:56,560 --> 00:54:58,400
I don't know
what you're talking about.

945
00:54:58,760 --> 00:55:01,200
All I can say is that Émilie
is a nice girl.

946
00:55:01,320 --> 00:55:03,920
Nice isn't a job.

947
00:55:06,360 --> 00:55:08,080
Brière, it's Marleau.

948
00:55:08,240 --> 00:55:09,640
Can you search

949
00:55:09,840 --> 00:55:12,800
for a nice hairdresser,
Émilie Guingamp?

950
00:55:13,200 --> 00:55:14,360
Like the train station.

951
00:55:14,680 --> 00:55:18,320
In exchange, I'll bring you
a nice florist.

952
00:55:18,480 --> 00:55:19,320
Yeah.

953
00:55:19,880 --> 00:55:21,760
We'll put her in custody.

954
00:55:23,200 --> 00:55:24,240
Carpentier!

955
00:55:24,640 --> 00:55:26,840
Can you put the girl in custody,
please?

956
00:55:27,240 --> 00:55:29,760
-Do you have the T.V. programs?
-No, Captain.

957
00:55:37,800 --> 00:55:40,320
-What are you doing?
-I was waiting for you.

958
00:55:41,640 --> 00:55:44,600
Come and look. The newspaper
published a photo of Chalard.

959
00:55:45,400 --> 00:55:47,080
I got you a copy.

960
00:55:47,520 --> 00:55:50,080
Where did they get that,
the scavengers?

961
00:55:50,240 --> 00:55:52,840
I don't know. I called,
but there was no response.

962
00:55:53,080 --> 00:55:56,320
Look at this.
I went through Chalard's accounts.

963
00:55:56,480 --> 00:55:57,680
Look what I found.

964
00:55:58,440 --> 00:56:00,320
I don't understand. What is it?

965
00:56:00,720 --> 00:56:04,480
