on high-risk loans.

966
00:56:04,640 --> 00:56:05,240
Yeah...

967
00:56:05,440 --> 00:56:08,480
Look, he also bet on the conditions
of a partnership,

968
00:56:08,680 --> 00:56:11,640
particularly on Ms. Dewaere's
animal park.

969
00:56:11,840 --> 00:56:13,760
He was desperate for money.

970
00:56:13,960 --> 00:56:16,760
Strange to kill a desperate man.

971
00:56:16,960 --> 00:56:19,120
-Usually, it's the opposite.
-True.

972
00:56:19,720 --> 00:56:23,200
He was also the owner
of Manon Bechet's florist.

973
00:56:23,520 --> 00:56:25,760
He wanted to turn it into
a golf shop.

974
00:56:25,960 --> 00:56:28,840
He even took her to court
to expel her.

975
00:56:29,320 --> 00:56:32,200
I don't think Manon Bechet
liked Monsieur Chalard,

976
00:56:32,320 --> 00:56:33,200
in my opinion.

977
00:56:35,040 --> 00:56:36,920
Good work, my boy.

978
00:56:37,120 --> 00:56:39,200
Go and get yourself a reward.

979
00:57:00,000 --> 00:57:02,080
-Mr. Gabriel?
-Yes, I'm here.

980
00:57:03,520 --> 00:57:07,000
Look what I found out the front.

981
00:57:09,520 --> 00:57:11,360
Do you know much about mushrooms?

982
00:57:11,560 --> 00:57:14,360
Me? Well, without boasting,
I'm the king of mushrooms.

983
00:57:14,680 --> 00:57:17,280
Mushrooms are easy.
There are only two categories:

984
00:57:17,480 --> 00:57:19,520
basidiomycetes and ascomycetes.

985
00:57:19,840 --> 00:57:23,040
Did you give any to Michel Chalard,
by chance?

986
00:57:23,560 --> 00:57:25,200
Yes, yesterday. Why?

987
00:57:25,360 --> 00:57:27,200
Do you know how many?

988
00:57:27,360 --> 00:57:28,920
Of course, there are some here.

989
00:57:31,240 --> 00:57:33,520
Go for it. They're yesterday's.
Smell that.

990
00:57:34,840 --> 00:57:36,200
Ah, gross.

991
00:57:37,040 --> 00:57:39,480
I don't like mushrooms.
I prefer music.

992
00:57:39,880 --> 00:57:42,720
I'm going to put something together

993
00:57:42,920 --> 00:57:45,760
for fans of "moderato cantabile."

994
00:57:47,640 --> 00:57:49,360
I'm have a pass
to Barbès National Orchestra,

995
00:57:49,520 --> 00:57:51,640
but it's not working.

996
00:57:51,800 --> 00:57:53,200
And I'm never wrong.

997
00:57:53,880 --> 00:57:54,760
Why do you ask?

998
00:57:55,160 --> 00:57:57,560
Because Michel Chalard
didn't die by hanging.

999
00:57:57,920 --> 00:57:59,120
Oh?

1000
00:57:59,920 --> 00:58:00,920
Are you sure?

1001
00:58:01,080 --> 00:58:03,200
On my mother's life...

1002
00:58:03,520 --> 00:58:04,360
who is dead.

1003
00:58:11,560 --> 00:58:12,960
Hello!

1004
00:58:14,800 --> 00:58:15,920
Guess why I'm here.

1005
00:58:17,240 --> 00:58:19,400
-No idea.
-At least guess.

1006
00:58:19,600 --> 00:58:21,000
You have to play to win.

1007
00:58:21,840 --> 00:58:23,680
-Come on!
-I don't want to guess.

1008
00:58:23,840 --> 00:58:25,200
Oh, come on!

1009
00:58:25,360 --> 00:58:27,760
I'm not in a joking mood today. OK?

1010
00:58:28,240 --> 00:58:29,960
You're no fun.

1011
00:58:30,480 --> 00:58:31,280
Look at this.

1012
00:58:34,520 --> 00:58:36,080
I know your methods.

1013
00:58:36,280 --> 00:58:38,200
You want me to react? It won't work.

1014
00:58:38,400 --> 00:58:40,800
Well, no reaction is a reaction.

1015
00:58:41,000 --> 00:58:43,200
My methods aren't so stupid,
you know.

1016
00:58:44,120 --> 00:58:46,080
Do you want my real opinion?

1017
00:58:47,080 --> 00:58:48,360
I didn't like him.

1018
00:58:48,760 --> 00:58:50,480
I won't pretend to be sad.

1019
00:58:50,960 --> 00:58:53,560
-Not even a little tear?
-No.

1020
00:58:53,760 --> 00:58:55,280
He didn't even deserve hate.

1021
00:58:55,800 --> 00:58:57,680
You think my sadness...

1022
00:58:58,200 --> 00:59:00,680
What you said was beautiful. Poetic.

1023
00:59:01,840 --> 00:59:04,000
Can I help you to feed them?

1024
00:59:04,520 --> 00:59:06,440
No? I'll wait, then.

1025
00:59:06,640 --> 00:59:07,880
We'll talk after.

1026
00:59:08,240 --> 00:59:11,120
Your little protégée is in custody.

1027
00:59:19,480 --> 00:59:21,480
Did you know about Chalard?

1028
00:59:21,680 --> 00:59:24,520
He was going to throw Manon
out of her shop.

1029
00:59:24,840 --> 00:59:26,560
-He was a bastard.
-There we go.

1030
00:59:26,720 --> 00:59:28,840
Finally, a swear word.

1031
00:59:29,240 --> 00:59:31,240
You keep animal fur.

1032
00:59:31,440 --> 00:59:33,640
Manon is a brave girl.

1033
00:59:34,840 --> 00:59:36,400
I helped her get on her feet.

1034
00:59:37,080 --> 00:59:38,480
But she's still fragile.

1035
00:59:39,080 --> 00:59:41,160
Chalard would have finished her.

1036
00:59:41,360 --> 00:59:42,560
So, to save her,

1037
00:59:42,760 --> 00:59:44,960
