1038
00:59:45,200 --> 00:59:47,440
That's more than dedication.
That's devotion.

1039
00:59:47,920 --> 00:59:50,400
It would have sent her over the edge.

1040
00:59:50,880 --> 00:59:51,720
I wanted to help.

1041
00:59:52,120 --> 00:59:54,720
How much?
To the point of killing Chalard?

1042
00:59:56,440 --> 00:59:58,440
Because...
you'll say it's a coincidence,

1043
00:59:58,640 --> 01:00:01,240
but just before dying, he told me:

1044
01:00:01,440 --> 01:00:03,560
"I have some revelations
about Ms. Dewaere."

1045
01:00:03,720 --> 01:00:04,480
Funny, no?

1046
01:00:05,800 --> 01:00:07,640
If you think I'm guilty,

1047
01:00:08,000 --> 01:00:09,280
just lock me up.

1048
01:00:09,480 --> 01:00:11,480
-Do you have a lawyer?
-Yes.

1049
01:00:11,920 --> 01:00:13,400
But he's not much fun.

1050
01:00:13,920 --> 01:00:15,080
I'll say nothing.

1051
01:00:17,040 --> 01:00:18,200
Like most of them.

1052
01:00:18,400 --> 01:00:21,000
Sorry, I have a call. Who's calling?

1053
01:00:22,120 --> 01:00:22,880
Yeah?

1054
01:00:23,920 --> 01:00:24,800
OK?

1055
01:00:25,120 --> 01:00:26,360
OK, cool.

1056
01:00:26,520 --> 01:00:27,400
See you soon.

1057
01:00:28,440 --> 01:00:30,000
Sorry, I have to go,

1058
01:00:30,320 --> 01:00:33,760
because your protégée
is less stubborn than you.

1059
01:00:33,880 --> 01:00:35,960
She's decided to speak. Great, right?

1060
01:00:36,160 --> 01:00:38,240
I swear, Manon isn't involved
in his death.

1061
01:00:38,400 --> 01:00:39,520
I swear.

1062
01:00:40,080 --> 01:00:41,360
We'll see... Inshallah.

1063
01:00:41,520 --> 01:00:42,960
I have a plus in my job:

1064
01:00:43,160 --> 01:00:45,920
I come across as so stupid
that people feel sorry for me,

1065
01:00:46,080 --> 01:00:47,960
they end up accusing each other.

1066
01:00:48,960 --> 01:00:51,240
Cool, right? Well, see you soon.

1067
01:00:52,840 --> 01:00:55,680
You know you're lucky
to be in custody with me?

1068
01:00:55,840 --> 01:00:57,000
One: I have no man,

1069
01:00:57,480 --> 01:00:59,480
two: I have no woman or children

1070
01:00:59,640 --> 01:01:01,280
and I don't have gastro.

1071
01:01:01,680 --> 01:01:04,320
So, I have all the time in the world.

1072
01:01:04,520 --> 01:01:05,520
I'm listening.

1073
01:01:06,880 --> 01:01:09,120
Why were you at Chalard's
the other night?

1074
01:01:09,720 --> 01:01:11,600
We wanted to protest his golf course.

1075
01:01:11,920 --> 01:01:13,000
We went with a banner.

1076
01:01:13,720 --> 01:01:14,880
Dressed as Zorro.

1077
01:01:15,760 --> 01:01:18,040
-We thought it was funny.
-Yeah.

1078
01:01:18,360 --> 01:01:20,600
Except someone was waiting
when you arrived.

1079
01:01:21,520 --> 01:01:22,520
There was a shot.

1080
01:01:22,720 --> 01:01:25,800
Yes, I know, from the guard,
with Chalard's Mauser,

1081
01:01:25,960 --> 01:01:28,000
which he'd lent him. OK, then?

1082
01:01:29,040 --> 01:01:30,360
Then, I ran off.

1083
01:01:31,200 --> 01:01:33,200
I went to Jeanne and she helped me.

1084
01:01:35,080 --> 01:01:35,960
And that's all.

1085
01:01:36,360 --> 01:01:37,840
That's all I know.

1086
01:01:39,040 --> 01:01:40,360
I hope for your case

1087
01:01:40,520 --> 01:01:43,400
that Chalard's mistress
didn't see you at his house.

1088
01:01:43,600 --> 01:01:46,160
-Why?
-Why? Because, one:

1089
01:01:46,800 --> 01:01:49,760
around his body was a bouquet
from your florist.

1090
01:01:50,160 --> 01:01:51,080
OK?

1091
01:01:51,600 --> 01:01:54,800
Two: you have a motive,

1092
01:01:54,920 --> 01:01:56,360
because your friend's dead.

1093
01:01:57,600 --> 01:02:01,040
And three: you have
a criminal record, my girl.

1094
01:02:01,400 --> 01:02:02,680
So, either you killed him,

1095
01:02:02,840 --> 01:02:05,040
or you have a very good alibi.

1096
01:02:06,360 --> 01:02:07,560
See what I'm saying?

1097
01:02:14,360 --> 01:02:15,240
Well?

1098
01:02:15,400 --> 01:02:17,440
-Is Chalard's mistress there?
-No.

1099
01:02:17,600 --> 01:02:19,360
I don't know why, at this time.

1100
01:02:19,520 --> 01:02:20,720
Her car's there.

1101
01:02:20,920 --> 01:02:22,600
We might find something.

1102
01:02:22,760 --> 01:02:23,720
Ah, yeah.

1103
01:02:25,680 --> 01:02:28,840
You're right! You're not so stupid.

1104
01:02:29,000 --> 01:02:30,040
Thanks.

1105
01:02:31,080 --> 01:02:32,320
Powerful car.

1106
01:02:33,120 --> 01:02:35,480
Let's have a look, then...

1107
01:02:35,960 --> 01:02:38,840
If I call Chalard, what will happen?

1108
01:02:42,120 --> 01:02:42,800
Voila...

1109
01:02:44,960 --> 01:02:46,800
There we go.

1110
01:02:48,520 --> 01:02:49,760
Is that Chalard's phone?

1111
01:02:49,960 --> 01:02:51,920
Yeah. It's like a frog Kama Sutra.

1112
01:02:52,120 --> 01:02:53,920
-Is it her?
-Yeah.

1113
01:02:54,240 --> 01:02:55,960
A crime of passion, then?

1114
01:02:56,120 --> 01:02:57,840
What's wrong? You seem upset.

1115
01:02:59,080 --> 01:02:59,720
A bit, yeah.

1116
01:02:59,920 --> 01:03:01,960
Murderers are like that.

1117
01:03:02,120 --> 01:03:04,520
Crimes are often completely stupid,

1118
01:03:04,680 --> 01:03:07,040
stupid phones...

1119
01:03:07,240 --> 01:03:09,320
I'll say this: murderers are often

1120
01:03:09,480 --> 01:03:11,080
are stupider than you think.

1121
01:03:12,240 --> 01:03:13,600
Hello!

1122
01:03:14,480 --> 01:03:15,920
Ms. Guingamp!

1123
01:03:16,800 --> 01:03:18,600
-My God, it's ugly.
-Yeah.

1124
01:03:19,240 --> 01:03:21,000
-Shall we go up?
-Yeah.

1125
01:03:24,280 --> 01:03:25,400
Ms. Guingamp?

1126
01:03:26,960 --> 01:03:28,080
Ms. Guingamp?

1127
01:03:33,520 --> 01:03:35,320
Remorse? Suicide?

1128
01:03:36,080 --> 01:03:38,520
No, she's asleep.
Go and make her a coffee.

1129
01:03:39,280 --> 01:03:41,360
Stop looking!

1130
01:03:41,840 --> 01:03:45,320
Make a strong coffee,
black with salt, so she vomits.

1131
01:03:46,120 --> 01:03:47,960
What's this? What a joke.

1132
01:03:48,840 --> 01:03:50,040
Not very practical.

1133
01:03:50,920 --> 01:03:52,520
Oh... earrings.

1134
01:03:54,080 --> 01:03:55,560
Chalard didn't want those on.

1135
01:03:58,040 --> 01:03:59,760
Ali Baba's cave.

1136
01:03:59,960 --> 01:04:01,720
Strange hairbrush.

1137
01:04:03,040 --> 01:04:06,000
Ah! Bunny ears.

1138
01:04:08,000 --> 01:04:09,560
Come on, honey.

1139
01:04:10,240 --> 01:04:12,080
Up you get!

1140
01:04:15,400 --> 01:04:17,680
Ms. Boulier, it's nice to see you.

1141
01:04:17,840 --> 01:04:19,600
Thanks for coming. Here.

1142
01:04:20,000 --> 01:04:21,280
See you soon?

1143
01:04:22,400 --> 01:04:25,200
Hello, ladies. How are you?

1144
01:04:25,360 --> 01:04:26,560
Everything going well?

1145
01:04:26,760 --> 01:04:28,320
Have a good day.
Thanks.

1146
01:04:29,080 --> 01:04:30,920
Hello.

1147
01:04:32,760 --> 01:04:33,760
What's this?

1148
01:04:35,080 --> 01:04:35,960
Can I count on you?

1149
01:04:36,160 --> 01:04:38,000
-Thanks, Mr. Mayor.
-Thanks, goodbye.

1150
01:04:38,160 --> 01:04:39,360
Goodbye.

1151
01:04:39,560 --> 01:04:41,120
Why aren't you picking up?

1152
01:04:41,840 --> 01:04:43,360
I followed you yesterday.

1153
01:04:43,520 --> 01:04:44,720
Hello, ma'am.

1154
01:04:44,920 --> 01:04:46,640
How are you? Have a good day.

1155
01:04:46,800 --> 01:04:48,240
I saw you go to his house.

1156
01:04:48,680 --> 01:04:51,120
-Do you think I killed him?
-You tell me.

1157
01:04:51,560 --> 01:04:53,520
-Hello, Mr. Mayor.
-Hello, ma'am.

1158
01:04:53,720 --> 01:04:56,080
-I'm awaiting your answer.
-Come to my office.

1159
01:04:56,240 --> 01:04:56,880
Goodbye.

1160
01:04:57,040 --> 01:04:59,040
You hated him for the golf course.

1161
01:04:59,200 --> 01:05:01,280
You go to his house, soon after
he's dead.

1162
01:05:01,400 --> 01:05:03,240
What should I think?

1163
01:05:04,080 --> 01:05:05,480
Do you think I killed him?

1164
01:05:05,800 --> 01:05:07,360
You never answer my questions.

1165
01:05:07,840 --> 01:05:09,720
Because you don't want to know.

1166
01:05:10,400 --> 01:05:12,920
-You don't like women with no past.
-You're wrong.

1167
01:05:13,120 --> 01:05:16,880
I searched your past
and wasn't disappointed.

1168
01:05:17,360 --> 01:05:18,840
Jeanne Ferrari. 12 years.

1169
01:05:19,240 --> 01:05:20,240
Eight.

1170
01:05:21,360 --> 01:05:24,120
An ex-inmate.

1171
01:05:24,560 --> 01:05:27,160
You don't hesitate
to throw away anyone with history.

1172
01:05:27,640 --> 01:05:29,280
If you want to turn me in,

1173
01:05:29,560 --> 01:05:31,080
don't worry, they already know.

1174
01:05:33,320 --> 01:05:34,440
Why didn't you say?

1175
01:05:35,160 --> 01:05:36,280
To avoid a reaction.

1176
01:05:37,600 --> 01:05:39,240
It looks like you don't know me.

1177
01:05:39,400 --> 01:05:40,000
Same for me.

1178
01:05:40,160 --> 01:05:41,800
I don't recognize you.

1179
01:05:42,360 --> 01:05:45,600
Your father and I crossed you off.

1180
01:05:47,080 --> 01:05:48,520
You're no longer our girl.

1181
01:05:50,680 --> 01:05:53,120
Who's this man in a suit
shaking people's hands?

1182
01:05:53,320 --> 01:05:55,760
Distributing flyers
to win the election?

1183
01:05:56,680 --> 01:05:57,840
I don't know him.

1184
01:05:58,000 --> 01:05:59,760
Come on, come on!

1185
01:06:04,920 --> 01:06:05,680
It was fun.

1186
01:06:07,560 --> 01:06:09,760
He read that strangling
helps the orgasm.

1187
01:06:10,880 --> 01:06:12,520
So, he wanted to try.

1188
01:06:13,160 --> 01:06:15,240
Sex makes you lose your head,
you know?

1189
01:06:15,800 --> 01:06:18,880
Well, you've lost your head
to the point of forgetting

1190
01:06:19,040 --> 01:06:20,400
Chalard's telephone.

1191
01:06:20,720 --> 01:06:22,000
We filmed each other.

1192
01:06:22,760 --> 01:06:24,840
I didn't want the sex-tape
to be seen.

1193
01:06:25,040 --> 01:06:27,280
I know some use that to get famous,

1194
01:06:27,440 --> 01:06:28,680
but I don't need that.

1195
01:06:28,880 --> 01:06:31,440
-The hairdressing's going well.
-I can see that.

1196
01:06:32,240 --> 01:06:35,680
So, he died before your eyes.

1197
01:06:36,160 --> 01:06:38,560
Yes.

1198
01:06:39,960 --> 01:06:42,400
I did the knot,

1199
01:06:42,560 --> 01:06:43,720
tightened it a bit,

1200
01:06:48,400 --> 01:06:49,880
then, he started coughing

1201
01:06:50,080 --> 01:06:51,960
and feeling unwell. So, I undid it.

1202
01:06:53,200 --> 01:06:55,280
But it got worse and worse. I tried

1203
01:06:55,480 --> 01:06:58,440
to undo the rope,
but it was strangling him.

1204
01:06:59,440 --> 01:07:02,160
I swear that's the truth.
I'd never hurt him.

1205
01:07:02,720 --> 01:07:04,280
But I was so scared...

1206
01:07:05,000 --> 01:07:07,040
I left straight away

1207
01:07:07,200 --> 01:07:08,760
and I took two pills.

1208
01:07:08,920 --> 01:07:10,600
I told myself to sleep on it.

1209
01:07:12,480 --> 01:07:14,160
I was going to come and see you.

1210
01:07:14,360 --> 01:07:17,680
I swear...
I was so scared.

1211
01:07:17,840 --> 01:07:18,960
I understand.

1212
01:07:19,160 --> 01:07:22,400
There's something not right
there, in your video,

1213
01:07:23,400 --> 01:07:24,880
which is short but trashy.

1214
01:07:25,080 --> 01:07:27,280
The casting is really good,

1215
01:07:27,440 --> 01:07:28,960
but the story's dated,

1216
01:07:29,160 --> 01:07:32,200
it's basic. Regarding the timing,

1217
01:07:32,520 --> 01:07:34,600
you need a new script, look...

1218
01:07:36,080 --> 01:07:37,320
He has no bottoms.

1219
01:07:38,120 --> 01:07:39,200
-Bottoms?
-Yeah,

1220
01:07:39,800 --> 01:07:43,480
that you put on the bottom
or the top, depending who you are.

1221
01:07:43,880 --> 01:07:45,120
Look, in this newspaper.

1222
01:07:45,280 --> 01:07:47,480
Far from suggesting
the media lies to us...

1223
01:07:48,120 --> 01:07:50,920
Look here, he's wearing bottoms

1224
01:07:51,120 --> 01:07:52,840
and lipstick.

1225
01:07:53,000 --> 01:07:55,640
While in the film, he isn't.
How is that?

1226
01:07:56,200 --> 01:07:57,200
Ask Jeanne Dewaere.

1227
01:07:57,960 --> 01:08:00,320
Why? Is she a funeral director?

1228
01:08:00,480 --> 01:08:01,840
She killed him.

1229
01:08:02,480 --> 01:08:05,800
When I arrived, Michel was so happy,
he said he had her.

1230
01:08:06,000 --> 01:08:08,480
That she had no choice but to accept.

1231
01:08:09,280 --> 01:08:11,880
-Calm down, ma'am!
-You're kidding!

1232
01:08:12,080 --> 01:08:14,680
I demand to see Captain Marleau.
I have a confession.

1233
01:08:14,840 --> 01:08:16,960
OK, guys, I'll take care of this.

1234
01:08:17,160 --> 01:08:19,000
How can I help you?

1235
01:08:19,200 --> 01:08:20,960
I can't let an innocent person
be accused.

1236
01:08:21,120 --> 01:08:22,840
I killed Michel Chalard.

1237
01:08:23,240 --> 01:08:24,480
The love of my life.

1238
01:08:24,680 --> 01:08:26,560
OK, I'm not a shrink. Sit down.

1239
01:08:26,720 --> 01:08:28,720
This will save you 50 euros.

1240
01:08:29,520 --> 01:08:31,160
I'm listening. What is it?

1241
01:08:32,200 --> 01:08:34,120
I'd had enough
of his debauched ways.

1242
01:08:34,720 --> 01:08:37,120
So, I poisoned his tea.

1243
01:08:37,800 --> 01:08:41,320
A dose strong enough for him to fall
asleep in her arms, rather than...

1244
01:08:43,880 --> 01:08:45,520
-Well, you understand.
-No.

1245
01:08:46,880 --> 01:08:48,400
I didn't want him to die.

1246
01:08:49,520 --> 01:08:51,920
I couldn't have known
it was dangerous.

1247
01:08:52,440 --> 01:08:53,880
Lord...

1248
01:08:54,080 --> 01:08:55,960
OK, Brière, you can let
Manon Bechet go.

1249
01:08:56,160 --> 01:08:58,080
-And the police squad?
-We don't care.

1250
01:08:58,240 --> 01:08:59,880
They won't care about a banner.

1251
01:09:00,080 --> 01:09:02,040
We don't put our noses
in their business.

1252
01:09:02,200 --> 01:09:03,040
And I like Zorro.

1253
01:09:03,200 --> 01:09:06,200
So, go and do the deed
my little munchkin.

1254
01:09:06,400 --> 01:09:08,280
As for you...
Into custody.

1255
01:09:08,760 --> 01:09:11,000
Rest and relaxation.

1256
01:09:12,080 --> 01:09:14,080
For a long time.

1257
01:09:22,760 --> 01:09:25,440
I was maybe the only one,
but I loved Michel Chalard.

1258
01:09:25,880 --> 01:09:27,440
How can I tell him now?

1259
01:09:36,840 --> 01:09:39,120
Poison. My god, what a joke.

1260
01:09:39,280 --> 01:09:42,040
I would have given him more
for what he did.

1261
01:09:42,240 --> 01:09:44,240
It brings us back
to Ms. Dewaere, then.

1262
01:09:44,680 --> 01:09:46,000
What are you doing?

1263
01:09:46,160 --> 01:09:48,000
Get out of here!

1264
01:09:48,360 --> 01:09:50,600
Ah... sorry.

1265
01:09:53,000 --> 01:09:54,360
Hello, Léopold?

1266
01:09:54,520 --> 01:09:57,040
Yeah, it's me. Yeah.

1267
01:09:58,680 --> 01:10:00,000
OK, I'm on my way.

1268
01:10:00,160 --> 01:10:01,680
Yes, I'm alone.

1269
01:10:02,200 --> 01:10:03,400
See you soon?

1270
01:10:09,840 --> 01:10:11,520
Do you understand what I felt?

1271
01:10:11,960 --> 01:10:13,240
Put yourself in my place.

1272
01:10:13,440 --> 01:10:15,600
I was with someone with a past
I had no idea about.

1273
01:10:15,800 --> 01:10:17,160
Let me digest it a little.

1274
01:10:17,880 --> 01:10:18,720
So?

1275
01:10:19,240 --> 01:10:20,880
This election is important.

1276
01:10:21,280 --> 01:10:22,240
I'll be frank:

1277
01:10:22,440 --> 01:10:25,440
in school, people called me
"the mayor," and I liked it.

1278
01:10:50,720 --> 01:10:52,240
I thought you were in custody.

1279
01:10:52,400 --> 01:10:53,320
I was.

1280
01:10:53,960 --> 01:10:55,520
With the funny policewoman.

1281
01:10:58,960 --> 01:11:01,440
I'm not sure if she's an idiot
or a real bitch.

1282
01:11:02,080 --> 01:11:03,680
Maybe she's really nice.

1283
01:11:04,160 --> 01:11:06,200
She's the first of her kind.

1284
01:11:06,800 --> 01:11:08,400
Well, she believed me.

1285
01:11:08,600 --> 01:11:10,600
I'm so relieved,
you wouldn't believe it.

1286
01:11:11,240 --> 01:11:14,280
She was strange but cool
at the same time.

1287
01:11:15,280 --> 01:11:17,960
Yeah, she's really strange. I agree.

1288
01:11:18,640 --> 01:11:20,640
-Do you want a coffee?
-Yes, please.

1289
01:11:27,680 --> 01:11:31,080
Jeanne, I want to warn you:
for Chalard's murder,

1290
01:11:31,600 --> 01:11:33,000
you're the prime suspect.

1291
01:11:47,480 --> 01:11:48,600
I'm afraid, Jeanne.

1292
01:11:49,160 --> 01:11:50,440
For you, this time.

1293
01:11:57,120 --> 01:12:00,040
Oscar! Here's Léopold.

1294
01:12:00,720 --> 01:12:04,360
Léopold, this is Oscar.
Alias: Nonos.

1295
01:12:04,560 --> 01:12:08,000
He doesn't seem like much now,
but as soon as he gets cold meat,

1296
01:12:08,160 --> 01:12:10,080
he comes to life.

1297
01:12:10,640 --> 01:12:12,960
And this is Léopold.
Alias: Popol,

1298
01:12:13,160 --> 01:12:15,560
the God of guts,

1299
01:12:15,760 --> 01:12:18,880
the Eric Clapton of intestines,
great lover of toxicology,

1300
01:12:19,080 --> 01:12:23,000
-among other things...
-Thank you, my friend.

1301
01:12:23,160 --> 01:12:25,960
My friends' friends are my friends.

1302
01:12:26,160 --> 01:12:28,960
And if they're in forensics,
obviously,

1303
01:12:29,120 --> 01:12:30,480
that's even better.

1304
01:12:32,320 --> 01:12:33,520
Léopold,

1305
01:12:33,720 --> 01:12:37,200
I'm sorry to make you work
secretly like this.

1306
01:12:37,360 --> 01:12:39,560
Not at all!

1307
01:12:39,720 --> 01:12:41,880
It reminds me of my student years,

1308
01:12:42,040 --> 01:12:44,160
when we stole hands from cadavers

1309
01:12:44,320 --> 01:12:46,600
to slide them in girls' pockets.

1310
01:12:48,080 --> 01:12:51,080
We filled intestines with water
and put them above the kitchen door.

1311
01:12:51,280 --> 01:12:53,760
It got my mom every time.

1312
01:12:53,920 --> 01:12:56,240
Intestines are always good.

1313
01:13:05,320 --> 01:13:09,200
What is this bucket of guts?

1314
01:13:17,560 --> 01:13:20,520
That's Chalard. Léopold! Here he is!

1315
01:13:21,200 --> 01:13:23,880
It reminds me of a famous
tripe recipe,

1316
01:13:24,040 --> 01:13:25,800
Well prepared tripe

1317
01:13:25,960 --> 01:13:27,680
is a sure way to heaven.

1318
01:13:27,880 --> 01:13:31,080
It's rare. Very rare, this.

1319
01:13:31,840 --> 01:13:33,760
And like everything rare,

1320
01:13:34,120 --> 01:13:35,520
it demands time

1321
01:13:35,680 --> 01:13:39,200
and infinite delicacy.

1322
01:13:39,400 --> 01:13:40,560
So, we'll take our time.

1323
01:13:41,360 --> 01:13:44,680
I'll leave you, then, boys,
with intestinal joys.

1324
01:13:44,840 --> 01:13:46,200
I have to work.

1325
01:13:53,320 --> 01:13:55,040
Come back quick, we'll miss you.

1326
01:14:03,600 --> 01:14:05,600
-The two of us.
-The three of us.

1327
01:14:12,440 --> 01:14:14,240
-Captain?
-I'm here.

1328
01:14:14,880 --> 01:14:17,520
-I have the lab results.
-Ah, great.

1329
01:14:17,680 --> 01:14:18,800
They worked hard.

1330
01:14:18,960 --> 01:14:20,520
I put pressure on them.

1331
01:14:20,720 --> 01:14:22,320
Bravo, my dear. Well done.

1332
01:14:22,440 --> 01:14:23,960
So, Chalard's photo was taken

1333
01:14:24,160 --> 01:14:27,200
with a Leica from 1956
with double viewfinders.

1334
01:14:27,360 --> 01:14:30,160
It's an incredible camera.
It'll catch a drop of dew.

1335
01:14:30,640 --> 01:14:31,840
OK.

1336
01:14:33,480 --> 01:14:35,200
We know it was developed at home.

1337
01:14:35,360 --> 01:14:36,600
That's good.

1338
01:14:37,240 --> 01:14:39,800
-And you?
-I'm working, if you can't see.

1339
01:14:40,000 --> 01:14:42,880
Because the murderer
is not here at the moment.

1340
01:14:43,080 --> 01:14:46,400
But the murderer always comes back
to the crime scene.

1341
01:14:46,560 --> 01:14:47,760
That's why I'm waiting.

1342
01:14:47,920 --> 01:14:49,400
Did you see? This book's good.

1343
01:14:49,600 --> 01:14:52,560
He wasn't lying, the guard.

1344
01:14:52,760 --> 01:14:56,080
His mushrooms were indeed edible.

1345
01:14:57,240 --> 01:14:58,160
Are you staying?

1346
01:14:58,600 --> 01:15:00,080
I told you, I'm waiting.

1347
01:15:00,280 --> 01:15:02,160
And I don't like threesomes,
so you can leave.

1348
01:15:03,440 --> 01:15:06,040
-Goodbye, Captain.
-Bye, honey.

1349
01:15:08,920 --> 01:15:12,400
So, inocybes...
What's that?

1350
01:16:14,600 --> 01:16:17,480
So, did someone lose her earring?

1351
01:16:21,200 --> 01:16:22,840
I came to see Chalard yesterday.

1352
01:16:24,640 --> 01:16:28,320
For good reason.
I heard about Manon's eviction.

1353
01:16:29,120 --> 01:16:30,360
I came to plead.

1354
01:16:31,040 --> 01:16:31,800
And?

1355
01:16:33,000 --> 01:16:35,080
And when I arrived, he was dead.

1356
01:16:35,240 --> 01:16:36,360
Chalard?

1357
01:16:45,120 --> 01:16:46,080
Chalard?

1358
01:17:00,640 --> 01:17:01,680
Chalard?

1359
01:17:28,840 --> 01:17:30,120
What time was it?

1360
01:17:30,560 --> 01:17:32,120
-2:15.
-Ah, yes.

1361
01:17:32,800 --> 01:17:34,520
The famous pocket watch.

1362
01:17:34,960 --> 01:17:36,160
It's a good watch.

1363
01:17:36,320 --> 01:17:38,200
On another note,

1364
01:17:38,400 --> 01:17:41,160
do you know someone
with a photo lab at home?

1365
01:17:42,200 --> 01:17:45,800
Someone who does portraits
a bit... fancy.

1366
01:17:46,240 --> 01:17:46,920
Why?

1367
01:17:47,080 --> 01:17:48,960
It's not for me. I prefer videos.

1368
01:17:49,160 --> 01:17:51,720
No, there's a local photographer

1369
01:17:51,920 --> 01:17:53,920
who immortalized Chalard
with a Leica.

1370
01:17:54,360 --> 01:17:56,840
So, I'd like to see him
to discuss antiques.

1371
01:17:57,000 --> 01:17:58,600
Do you know anyone?

1372
01:17:59,280 --> 01:18:01,320
I don't know. Not me, anyway.

1373
01:18:03,080 --> 01:18:05,400
OK. You can go, then.

1374
01:18:06,440 --> 01:18:07,120
Is it a trap?

1375
01:18:07,560 --> 01:18:09,920
You're completely paranoid!

1376
01:18:10,120 --> 01:18:12,440
I'll keep the earring,
you can go home.

1377
01:18:12,640 --> 01:18:15,000
Do you want to sleep with me?
I snore.

1378
01:18:16,000 --> 01:18:17,040
Do you mind?

1379
01:18:21,080 --> 01:18:22,360
Goodnight.

1380
01:18:41,280 --> 01:18:42,520
They're beautiful, right?

1381
01:18:44,440 --> 01:18:46,120
I need to speak to you.

1382
01:18:52,600 --> 01:18:53,640
Why?

1383
01:18:55,440 --> 01:18:59,240
The cop mentioned a Leica that
was used to take a photo of the body.

1384
01:19:00,640 --> 01:19:02,240
I didn't say, but I know who has one.

1385
01:19:03,360 --> 01:19:04,400
Why?

1386
01:19:06,240 --> 01:19:07,400
For Arthur.

1387
01:19:07,800 --> 01:19:08,840
What?

1388
01:19:13,880 --> 01:19:15,080
When he was killed

1389
01:19:16,760 --> 01:19:19,040
in an apparent hunting accident,

1390
01:19:21,360 --> 01:19:22,800
we were together, him and me,

1391
01:19:24,400 --> 01:19:25,520
in the clearing,

1392
01:19:26,320 --> 01:19:27,400
on Chalard's land.

1393
01:19:33,000 --> 01:19:36,760
Go and do your business elsewhere!

1394
01:19:43,360 --> 01:19:44,160
Arthur...

1395
01:19:48,160 --> 01:19:49,120
Arthur!

1396
01:19:51,680 --> 01:19:53,040
Arthur!

1397
01:19:54,560 --> 01:19:56,240
The police opened an investigation,

1398
01:19:56,440 --> 01:19:57,840
but no one found the killer.

1399
01:19:58,680 --> 01:19:59,840
The case was filed away.

1400
01:20:00,320 --> 01:20:01,320
Why say nothing?

1401
01:20:01,480 --> 01:20:03,120
It was my revenge.

1402
01:20:05,360 --> 01:20:06,800
I never saw his face.

1403
01:20:07,960 --> 01:20:09,640
I never saw who fired.

1404
01:20:11,400 --> 01:20:12,920
But I swore, one day I'd know.

1405
01:20:13,760 --> 01:20:14,600
Why now?

1406
01:20:15,280 --> 01:20:18,320
All I knew was that he was killed
by a Mauser 43.

1407
01:20:19,160 --> 01:20:20,960
When the police spoke, I understood.

1408
01:20:32,800 --> 01:20:34,120
Don't move!

1409
01:20:34,480 --> 01:20:37,240
-What's going on?
-You're involved, too.

1410
01:20:37,400 --> 01:20:38,840
You're the key piece.

1411
01:20:39,320 --> 01:20:41,240
You still don't know
who killed Chalard?

1412
01:20:41,840 --> 01:20:44,760
This piece that will
let you heal morbillivirus?

1413
01:20:44,920 --> 01:20:46,480
Your Calabar bean.

1414
01:20:47,360 --> 01:20:49,760
You know who killed Chalard? You.

1415
01:20:50,680 --> 01:20:51,640
No one will believe it.

1416
01:20:51,840 --> 01:20:54,400
-Oh, yes!
-I don't have a motive.

1417
01:20:54,840 --> 01:20:56,840
You wanted to heal...

1418
01:20:57,000 --> 01:20:58,080
-You wanted revenge
-Let me go!

1419
01:20:58,280 --> 01:21:00,120
for your protégés Léonard and Manon!

1420
01:21:00,360 --> 01:21:02,680
Everyone knows your penchant
for delinquents.

1421
01:21:02,840 --> 01:21:04,400
And you've lost this one.

1422
01:21:06,760 --> 01:21:08,960
You know I've always tried
to help you.

1423
01:21:09,480 --> 01:21:11,960
If you'd spoken about Arthur earlier,

1424
01:21:12,120 --> 01:21:13,800
I would have done what I could.

1425
01:21:14,000 --> 01:21:16,240
You accepted the police's version.

1426
01:21:16,840 --> 01:21:18,640
No questions asked.

1427
01:21:19,280 --> 01:21:22,400
Arthur trusted you,
and you left him hanging.

1428
01:21:22,560 --> 01:21:24,120
Like all the others.

1429
01:21:26,840 --> 01:21:28,040
Let me go!

1430
01:21:29,760 --> 01:21:30,680
Let me go!

1431
01:21:50,480 --> 01:21:52,360
We're here, dear.

1432
01:21:52,520 --> 01:21:54,000
Did you see the newspaper?

1433
01:21:54,160 --> 01:21:56,560
They put a nice suit on Chalard.

1434
01:21:56,840 --> 01:21:59,680
"Shocking pants
for a fashionable man."

1435
01:21:59,840 --> 01:22:01,560
Well, there's the epitaph...

1436
01:22:01,720 --> 01:22:03,280
1987. Léopold Salaun.

1437
01:22:04,000 --> 01:22:06,240
The forensic scientist
from the Angoulême murders.

1438
01:22:06,400 --> 01:22:07,360
Am I right?

1439
01:22:07,760 --> 01:22:10,400
-Wait, no way.
-You've had some night. Tell us.

1440
01:22:10,560 --> 01:22:12,680
So, first point:

1441
01:22:13,400 --> 01:22:15,280
Michel Chalard

1442
01:22:15,400 --> 01:22:19,400
died between 12:30 and 1:00 p.m.

1443
01:22:19,880 --> 01:22:23,000
-Are you sure?
-100%

1444
01:22:23,400 --> 01:22:28,800
More precisely, I bet 12:50
and Oscar...

1445
01:22:28,960 --> 01:22:31,280
12:42, 12:43, maximum.

1446
01:22:31,400 --> 01:22:34,080
Second point: the weapon

1447
01:22:34,280 --> 01:22:37,760
-was an African bean.
-No?

1448
01:22:37,960 --> 01:22:39,400
-Physostigma.
-Yeah?

1449
01:22:39,600 --> 01:22:41,560
A plant used for exorcism rituals.

1450
01:22:41,800 --> 01:22:44,800
It has incredible
medicinal capacities,

1451
01:22:44,960 --> 01:22:46,960
but, as always,

1452
01:22:47,120 --> 01:22:48,840
it has a double effect.

1453
01:22:49,000 --> 01:22:52,240
It can heal or... kill.

1454
01:22:52,440 --> 01:22:55,080
Lethal dose: 0.2 milligrams.
Do you realize?

1455
01:22:56,320 --> 01:22:59,560
By grinding it, it's very easy
to hide in food

1456
01:22:59,720 --> 01:23:03,680
or to inject in a mushroom.

1457
01:23:03,840 --> 01:23:04,840
Ah...

1458
01:23:06,040 --> 01:23:07,520
And who has a plantation?

1459
01:23:08,400 --> 01:23:11,120
Plantations for medical research?

1460
01:23:11,280 --> 01:23:13,120
And who has an off-limit greenhouse?

1461
01:23:34,120 --> 01:23:35,280
Well, my dear?

1462
01:23:35,440 --> 01:23:38,080
The key is in the ignition.
Nothing strange.

1463
01:23:38,280 --> 01:23:40,800
-We didn't find Ms. Dewaere's truck.
-Damn.

1464
01:23:41,000 --> 01:23:43,280
I'll call Brière.
Thanks.

1465
01:23:45,640 --> 01:23:46,760
Yeah, it's me.

1466
01:23:46,920 --> 01:23:49,080
Can you send out a search
for Ms. Dewaere?

1467
01:23:49,240 --> 01:23:51,720
And give her truck's license plate.

1468
01:23:51,840 --> 01:23:52,840
Thanks.

1469
01:23:53,240 --> 01:23:54,000
-Hello.
-Hello.

1470
01:23:54,160 --> 01:23:55,000
-Are you OK?
-Yes.

1471
01:23:55,200 --> 01:23:56,960
You're wrong if you suspect her.

1472
01:23:57,120 --> 01:23:58,440
She's a good person.

1473
01:23:58,640 --> 01:24:00,080
She saved my life.

1474
01:24:01,840 --> 01:24:03,000
Did she say something?

1475
01:24:03,280 --> 01:24:04,720
No, I didn't see her.

1476
01:24:04,880 --> 01:24:07,560
I heard her car start,
but at 5:00 a.m., I'm in bed.

1477
01:24:08,840 --> 01:24:10,000
Captain!

1478
01:24:11,400 --> 01:24:12,400
I'm here!

1479
01:24:12,840 --> 01:24:14,120
I found the weapon.

1480
01:24:15,720 --> 01:24:16,800
Looks like mussels.

1481
01:24:17,160 --> 01:24:18,440
No, I don't think so.

1482
01:24:21,840 --> 01:24:22,840
Ah, OK.

1483
01:24:23,040 --> 01:24:25,560
Was she working on bean medication?

1484
01:24:25,760 --> 01:24:27,280
Is that how Michel died?

1485
01:24:27,480 --> 01:24:30,120
Can I have a look around, sir?

1486
01:24:30,600 --> 01:24:31,840
-Of course.
-After you.

1487
01:24:32,040 --> 01:24:33,280
-Yes.
-OK.

1488
01:24:38,240 --> 01:24:40,280
I have something for you. Come here.

1489
01:24:42,080 --> 01:24:43,720
I've always been loyal to her.

1490
01:24:43,880 --> 01:24:44,960
I'd give her my life.

1491
01:24:45,360 --> 01:24:48,280
I trust you.
You're not going to arrest me.

1492
01:24:48,440 --> 01:24:49,960
No, I'm not the type.

1493
01:24:50,120 --> 01:24:51,720
What did I do with it?

1494
01:24:52,560 --> 01:24:53,680
There it is.

1495
01:24:57,920 --> 01:24:59,400
Michel wanted me to testify.

1496
01:24:59,840 --> 01:25:00,880
About what?

1497
01:25:01,040 --> 01:25:03,120
That I found these in her bins.

1498
01:25:03,760 --> 01:25:05,360
Just before they were emptied.

1499
01:25:07,680 --> 01:25:10,440
Will that get me into trouble?

1500
01:25:10,600 --> 01:25:12,240
I don't know.

1501
01:25:12,960 --> 01:25:15,280
Michel is a good guy.

1502
01:25:16,280 --> 01:25:17,440
We grew up together.

1503
01:25:18,760 --> 01:25:20,120
It's a real shame.

1504
01:25:21,720 --> 01:25:24,720
Oh, Gaby...
you know what my mom said?

1505
01:25:24,880 --> 01:25:28,840
She said: "the best liars are those
who know how to shut up."

1506
01:25:37,960 --> 01:25:39,320
Hi, guys. It's not warm, eh?

1507
01:25:39,680 --> 01:25:41,080
I'm off to the dump.

1508
01:25:41,240 --> 01:25:42,440
It's only open today.

1509
01:25:42,600 --> 01:25:44,600
-No, you can't leave.
-Really?

1510
01:25:44,920 --> 01:25:47,440
It's OK. We've searched it.

1511
01:25:47,600 --> 01:25:49,280
-Go on.
-Thanks, guys.

1512
01:25:49,480 --> 01:25:50,680
-Goodbye.
-You coming?

1513
01:25:57,920 --> 01:25:59,720
-How are you?
-Good.

1514
01:26:36,960 --> 01:26:39,160
Do you believe Jeanne
could have killed him?

1515
01:26:39,920 --> 01:26:40,600
No.

1516
01:26:41,040 --> 01:26:43,240
You don't think so or you know so?

1517
01:26:43,720 --> 01:26:45,600
Did she speak about her past?

1518
01:26:45,800 --> 01:26:47,000
-Yeah.
-Ah, yeah?

1519
01:26:47,160 --> 01:26:49,280
Did she speak about prison, her ex,

1520
01:26:49,480 --> 01:26:51,120
the robberies, all of it?

1521
01:26:54,440 --> 01:26:55,840
Jeanne never lied to me.

1522
01:26:56,720 --> 01:26:58,440
-I knew it all along.
-Be careful.

1523
01:26:58,920 --> 01:27:02,600
Because a false testimony can
not only send a President tumbling,

1524
01:27:02,760 --> 01:27:04,560
but a mayor, too.

1525
01:27:04,760 --> 01:27:06,880
-So, are you sure?
-Yes.

1526
01:27:09,680 --> 01:27:11,440
You know the day he was killed,

1527
01:27:11,600 --> 01:27:13,880
Jeanne was at his house?
She left an earring.

1528
01:27:14,280 --> 01:27:15,760
I know.

1529
01:27:15,960 --> 01:27:17,000
I followed her.

1530
01:27:17,200 --> 01:27:19,240
-What time was it?
-Just past 2:00 p.m.

1531
01:27:20,920 --> 01:27:24,160
-But I really thought Jeanne...
-It's OK, you've cleared her.

1532
01:27:24,560 --> 01:27:26,600
Chalard was already dead at 2:00 p.m.

1533
01:27:27,000 --> 01:27:28,160
If she killed him,

1534
01:27:28,320 --> 01:27:31,160
I don't know why
she would have come back.

1535
01:27:31,280 --> 01:27:32,320
Unless she's sly.

1536
01:27:33,040 --> 01:27:33,720
-No.
-No.

1537
01:27:33,880 --> 01:27:35,160
Why are you here?

1538
01:27:35,440 --> 01:27:37,960
I wanted to know something:

1539
01:27:38,160 --> 01:27:40,440
your guard... what's his name...
Gabriel,

1540
01:27:40,600 --> 01:27:41,840
does he have a Leica?

1541
01:27:43,480 --> 01:27:45,480
-You know, to take photos.
-Yes.

1542
01:27:45,960 --> 01:27:47,040
There we go.

1543
01:27:48,000 --> 01:27:50,960
Thank you, Mr. Alain.

1544
01:27:53,760 --> 01:27:54,960
Good luck!

1545
01:27:59,760 --> 01:28:01,560
Don't move.
Don't move!

1546
01:28:03,440 --> 01:28:04,680
Where are you taking me?

1547
01:28:16,840 --> 01:28:18,400
What is it?

1548
01:28:18,560 --> 01:28:20,720
He said he was off to the dump.

1549
01:28:20,880 --> 01:28:23,400
And, as the truck had been checked...

1550
01:28:23,600 --> 01:28:25,720
He's not there. We don't know
where he is.

1551
01:28:25,880 --> 01:28:27,000
OK. What else?

1552
01:28:27,200 --> 01:28:29,440
We found Ms. Dewaere's car hidden
in the wood,

1553
01:28:29,640 --> 01:28:32,680
with her purse, her bank card,
her driving license.

1554
01:28:32,880 --> 01:28:34,880
It doesn't seem
like she left voluntarily.

1555
01:28:35,000 --> 01:28:36,720
Go and check the guard's lodge.

1556
01:28:36,880 --> 01:28:39,880
Then, meet me there.

1557
01:28:44,200 --> 01:28:45,720
What does he want?

1558
01:28:49,440 --> 01:28:51,200
Why did you come back?

1559
01:28:51,400 --> 01:28:53,560
We'll find her. Don't worry.

1560
01:28:53,720 --> 01:28:55,880
Stop following me. It annoys me.

1561
01:28:56,000 --> 01:28:57,280
You're very clingy.

1562
01:28:57,920 --> 01:28:59,920
-Captain! Captain!
-What is it?

1563
01:29:00,160 --> 01:29:01,480
-Come and see.
-What?

1564
01:29:01,640 --> 01:29:03,200
Didn't you understand?

1565
01:29:05,440 --> 01:29:07,320
This is where she must have been.

1566
01:29:09,880 --> 01:29:10,920
What's that?

1567
01:29:13,320 --> 01:29:17,280
Your girlfriend said she'd
never collaborate with cops.

1568
01:29:17,440 --> 01:29:18,880
She left us this.

1569
01:29:19,000 --> 01:29:20,840
But she didn't say the destination.

1570
01:29:21,040 --> 01:29:22,480
